# NeuroPulse — Hardware Architecture

> **Biopotential Sensing · Signal Processing · Real-Time Monitoring**

---

## System Overview

The NeuroPulse system integrates **ECG signal acquisition**, **multi-stage amplification**, **high-resolution ADC conversion**, and **ESP32-based processing**, along with real-time visualization and environmental sensing — engineered for precision biopotential monitoring.

---

## Signal Flow Architecture

```
AD8232  ──►  AD620  ──►  TL072  ──►  LM358  ──►  ADS1115  ──►  ESP32
 ECG        Instr.       Op-Amp      Op-Amp      16-bit ADC    Controller
 Module     Amp
```

---

## ESP32 Pin Configuration

### Sensor & ADC Interface

| Component | Pin  | Connected To   |
|-----------|------|----------------|
| AD8232    | OUT  | AD620 (S+)     |
| AD8232    | GND  | AD620 (S-)     |
| AD620     | VOUT | TL072 (Pin 3)  |
| TL072     | Pin 1| LM358 (Pin 3)  |
| LM358     | Pin 1| ADS1115 (A0)   |
| ADS1115   | SCL  | GPIO 22        |
| ADS1115   | SDA  | GPIO 21        |
| ADS1115   | ADDR | GND            |

