---

## Signal Conditioning — Gain Configuration

```
TL072  → Pin 1 ↔ Pin 2  [100 kΩ]
LM358  → Pin 1 ↔ Pin 2  [100 kΩ]
         Pin 2 → GND    [Additional gain path]
```

Used for **signal amplification and filtering of ECG signals**.

---

## Components

### Core Controller
- ESP32 (30-pin)

### Analog Front-End
- AD8232 — ECG Module
- AD620 — Instrumentation Amplifier
- TL072 — Op-Amp
- LM358 — Op-Amp

### Data Acquisition
- ADS1115 — 16-bit ADC

### Sensors
- MAX30102 — Heart Rate & SpO₂
- DHT11 — Temperature & Humidity

### Output Modules
- TFT SPI Display
- RGB LED

### Input Controls
- Rotary Encoder
- Toggle Switch

### Passive Components
- 100 kΩ Resistors (Gain)
- 10 kΩ Pull-up Resistor
- 220 Ω Resistors (LED Current Limiting)

---

## Design Notes

- I2C Bus is **shared** between ADS1115 and MAX30102
- Keep analog wiring **short and shielded** to reduce noise
- Ensure proper **common ground** across all subsystems
- Optimized for **low-noise ECG signal acquisition**

